<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[101610]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Women in Afghanistan]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[Palau Robert houses an exhibition showing the difficult situation of women in 'Afghanistan with photos by Gervasio Sánchez and texts by Mònica Bernabé.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>The Association for Human Rights in Afghanistan (ASDHA) makes known the difficult situation of women in &#8216;Afghanistan 13 years after the fall of the Taliban regime in an exhibition with photos by Gervasio Sánchez and texts by Mònica Bernabé.</p>
<p>The exhibition depicts violence against women in &#8216;Afghanistan as an endemic, structural phenomenon, a social problem aggravated by the war which goes virtually unpunished in the country, accompanied by a lack of education and the instrumentalisation of religion and chauvinistic laws.</p>
